          "en": "The time-complexity for computing the SVD factorization of an arbitrary \\\\(m \\times n\\\\) matrix is $$\\alpha (m^2n + n^3)$$, where the constant $$\\alpha$$ ranges from 4 to 10 (or more) depending on the algorithm.\n\nIn general, we can define the cost as: $$\\mathcal{O}(m^2n + n^3)$$\n\n<div class=\"figure\"> <img src=\"/math-lab/cs357-assets/figs/svd_graph.png\" height=300 width=600/> </div>"
